SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:children,play,toddler,museum,family
DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Pretend City Children's Museum - Events\\nCost: Fre
 e\\nDistance: 5.8 miles from home\\n\\nJoin us for a free evening where ch
 ildren and caretakers are invited to play in a sensory-friendly\, neuro-af
 firming environment! We encourage the whole family to attend\, and therapi
 sts can join as well.\nNeurodivergent Family Nights are held on the second
  Tuesday and fourth Thursday of each month from 5-7 pm (after we close to 
 general admission).\nOn these nights\, we dim the lights in the museum\, t
 urn off the sounds\, and offer a limited capacity of 250 guests. Staff are
  happy and ready to assist with providing various materials\, including no
 ise-cancelling headphones\, fidget toys\, sunglasses\, and weighted materi
 als for your convenience.\nRSVP HERE\n*Registration is required and opens 
 two weeks before each event. \nPlay Partners:\nPhilharmonic Society Music
  Mobile: Arriving in a Music Mobile van full of instruments\, Philharmoni
 c Society docents introduce the symphony orchestra and musical concepts wi
 th an engaging 30-minute presentation and instrument petting zoo\, giving 
 students the opportunity to try out different instruments in this hands-on
  experience. \nhttps://www.philharmonicsociety.org/education-community/ed
 ucation-programs/elementary/music-mobile\\n\\nMore info: https://www.prete
 ndcity.org/events/neurodivergent-family-night-3-2026-02-26-2026-03-26/
LOCATION:Pretend City Children's Museum - Events\, 29 Hubble\, Irvine\, CA
 \, 92618
URL:https://www.pretendcity.org/events/neurodivergent-family-night-3-2026-
 02-26-2026-03-26/
