  5.8 miles from home\\n\\nGet ready to rock\, roll\, sway\, sing\, and bop
 ! Because we’re bringing back Kidstock Music &amp\; Arts Festival! Enjoy
  live musical performances throughout the week and explore a mix of musica
 l styles! Because of your generosity during Igniting Potential\, Kidstock 
 will be bigger\, brighter\, and more hands-on than ever!\n3/31\n\n11 am: T
 he Rhythm Child Network\n2:30 pm: Pacific Dance\n\n\n4/1\n\n11 am: Ashley 
 Mills Monaghan\n2:30 pm: Jukie Davie\n\n\n4/2\n\n11 am &amp\; 2:30 pm Drum
 atiX\n\n\n4/3\n\n11 am: Conga Kids\n2:30 pm: Philharmonic Society’s Oran
 ge County Youth Symphony musicians\n\n\n4/4\n\n11 am: SoCal Drum Party\n1 
 pm: Bhangra by Nature\n\n4/5 CLOSED for Easter\nWeek 2\n4/7\n\n11 am &amp\
 ; 2:30 pm Fouta Toro West African Dance and Drum Ensemble\n\n4/8\n\n11 am:
  Backhaus Dance\n2:30 pm: Mommy Center Music\n\n4/9\n\n11 am: WeBreak Hip-
 Hop Dance Company\n2:30 pm: Ufirst Artist\n\n4/10\n\n11 am &amp\; 2:30 pm:
  Platinum Performing Arts\n\n4/11\n\n11 am: El Centro Cultural de México\
 n1 pm: The Portobellas\n2:30 pm: Kymberly Stewart\n\nThis exhibit is inclu
 ded in museum admission. Space is limited! Book your tickets now. \nEv
 ent DetailsMarch 31 – April 11Performance times vary by daySpring Break 
 hours: Tuesday–Sunday\, 10 am–4 pmClosed April 5 for EasterEvents subj
 ect to change.\nFAQs\nIs Kidstock included with admission?Yes. All perform
 ances are included with regular museum admission.\nWhat ages is Kidstock b
 est for?The festival is designed for children ages 0–8 and their familie
 s.\nDo performances happen every day?Yes. Live music or dance performances
  take place daily during the festival\, except when the museum is closed.\
 \n\\nMore info: https://www.pretendcity.org/events/kidstock/
LOCATION:Pretend City Children's Museum - Events\, 29 Hubble\, Irvine\, CA
 \, 92618
URL:https://www.pretendcity.org/events/kidstock/
