DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Pretend City Children's Museum - Events\\nCost: Fre
 e\\nDistance: 5.8 miles from home\\n\\nJoin us for a free evening where ch
 ildren and caretakers are invited to play in a sensory-friendly\, neuro-af
 firming environment! We encourage the whole family to attend\, and therapi
 sts can join as well.\nNeurodivergent Family Nights are held on the second
  Tuesday and fourth Thursday of each month from 5-7 pm (after we close to 
 general admission).\nOn these nights\, we dim the lights in the museum\, t
 urn off the sounds\, and offer a limited capacity of 250 guests. Staff are
  happy and ready to assist with providing various materials\, including no
 ise-cancelling headphones\, fidget toys\, sunglasses\, and weighted materi
 als for your convenience.\nRSVP COMING SOON\n*Registration is required and
  opens two weeks before each event. \nPlay Partners TBD\\n\\nMore info: h
